{"id":"1307.0923","submitter":"Ramil Akzyanov","authors":"R.S. Akzyanov, A.V. Rozhkov, A.L. Rakhmanov and Franco Nori","title":"Tunneling spectrum of a pinned vortex with a robust Majorana state","comments":"10 pages, 6 figures","journal-ref":"PhysRevB 89, 085409, (2014)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevB.89.085409","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.str-el","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We study a heterostructure which consists of a topological insulator and a\nsuperconductor with a hole. The hole pins a vortex. The system supports a\nrobust Majorana fermion state bound to the vortex core. We investigate the\npossibility of using scanning tunneling spectroscopy (i) to detect the Majorana\nfermion in the proposed setup and (ii) to study excited states bound to the\nvortex core. The Majorana fermion manifests itself as a magnetic-field\ndependent zero-bias anomaly of the tunneling conductance. Optimal parameters\nfor detecting Majorana fermions have been obtained. In the optimal regime, the\nMajorana fermion is separated from the excited states by a substantial gap. The\nnumber of zero-energy states equals the number of flux quanta in the hole;\nthus, the strength of the zero-bias anomaly depends on the magnetic field. The\nlowest energy excitations bound to the core are also studied. The excited\nstates spectrum differs from the spectrum of a typical Abrikosov vortex,\nproviding additional indirect confirmation of the Majorana state observation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Jul 2013 06:47:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 25 Mar 2014 13:26:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-03-26"}
