lent to a certain cyclotomic KLR-algebra. This allows us to\ndetermine the split Grothendieck group K_0(K_S), to show that its center is\nisomorphic to the cohomology ring of a certain Spaltenstein variety, and to\nprove that K_S is a graded cellular algebra.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Jul 2013 13:43:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-07-13"}
