lose to that of play in game\nsemantics that allows an easier handling of the interaction: the unfolding of\ninteraction is a path common to two interacting designs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Jul 2013 14:40:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Oct 2013 19:34:28 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 28 Mar 2015 20:26:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-01"}
